## Scripts
- `{{CHECK_CMD}}` — full CI check
- `{{TEST_CMD}}` — run tests
- `{{LINT_CMD}}` — lint

## Autonomous Workflow Rules

### Before Committing
- Always run `{{CHECK_CMD}}` before committing. If it fails, fix and re-run until it passes.
- Do NOT use `--no-verify` to skip git hooks.

### After Pushing / Creating a PR
- After every `git push` or `gh pr create`, get the run ID with `gh run list --branch <branch> --limit 1 --json databaseId --jq '.[0].databaseId'` then run `gh run watch <run-id> --exit-status`.
- If CI fails: read the logs with `gh run view <run-id> --log-failed`, fix the issue, commit, push, and watch CI again.
- Do not move on to the next task until CI is green.

### Branch Workflow
- NEVER commit directly to main. Always create a feature branch first.
- Branch naming: `feat/<short-description>`, `fix/<short-description>`, `chore/<short-description>`.
- After CI passes on the feature branch, create a PR with `gh pr create`.
- Do NOT push directly to main. All changes reach main via PR only.
- Always squash merge PRs: `gh pr merge <number> --squash --delete-branch`.
- After merging, checkout main and pull: `git checkout main && git pull`.

### Autonomous Issue Implementation
- When implementing an issue autonomously:
  - Read the full issue body — it contains all context needed.
  - Follow TDD strictly: one test -> red -> implement -> green -> repeat.
  - Derive the behavior list from the issue's Test Plan and Acceptance Criteria — do not ask the user for confirmation.
  - After all tests pass, run `{{CHECK_CMD}}` before committing.
  - If `{{CHECK_CMD}}` or tests fail, fix and retry. Do NOT skip or weaken tests.
  - Do NOT modify or delete tests from previous issues to make yours pass. If they conflict, stop and report the conflict.
  - Do NOT change public interfaces established by previous issues unless the current issue explicitly requires it.

### Regression Prevention
- Before starting work on any issue, run `{{TEST_CMD}}` and record the count of passing tests.
- After your implementation, the passing test count must be >= the starting count.
- NEVER delete or modify existing test files unless the current issue explicitly requires changing that behavior.
